    "It is now a socio-technical system, not just a technical system.",
    "A participant in [G7] commented on the perceived limitations of AI systems, suggesting that they are so complex that sometimes, they are not able to minimise ethical issues despite trying their best: ɓ \"I can say, yeah OK that was a fault, but this is how we did safety analysis.",
    "And I can see that this was missed, not because we were negligent, but just because it is so complicated.",
    "In this case, somebody died, but we did have the right ethical framework.",
    "But sometimes accidents happen."
